{{wikipedia}}
==English==

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/ˈdʒeɪkəb/}}
*{{SAMPA|/"dZeIk@b/}}

===Etymology===
From Late Latin [[Iacobus]] < Greek [[Ιάκωβος]] < Hebrew [[יעקב]] (''ya'aqov'', heel-grabber) < [[עקב]] (''‘akev'', [[heel]] of the foot). Cognates include [[James]] and [[Jim]].

===Proper noun===
'''Jacob'''

#(''Bible'') One of the sons of [[Isaac]] and [[Rebeccah]], and brother of [[Esau]]
#a male [[given name]].
